<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6844&amp;p=83456#p83456"><![CDATA[
I just took a multimeter to my NES and it seems that Expansion port pin 21 is connected to Emitter of Q1 (A397) i.e. VIDEO (since Q1's base connects to pin 21 of PPU i.e. Composite Video, and Audio is on pin 22 of Expansion port. Which is the reverse of the pinout on the NESDev Wiki for NES (Expansion port pinout webpage).<br /><br />I did a search and this seemed to be the best place to post this. Seeing as how I can't even enter the discussion on the editing on that Wiki.<br /><br />Regards,<br /><br />Alistair G.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4560">Live_Steam_Mad</a> — Sat Sep 03, 2011 3:01 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
