<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6844&amp;p=66030#p66030"><![CDATA[
I'm making some headway witht he NESpander Dev board, and I want to ask the community to verify a few things for me, so I don't mess anything up...<br /><br />#1:<br /><br />NES EXP Vs. FC EXP Ports<br />I used a variety of references that I found on several sites, including the NESDev Wiki, some of which were conflicting or incomplete... The FC EXP port isn't seemingly in the NESDev Wiki files either...so I located one by Kevin Horton plus two others, plus the schematic of the FC in the FAQ and used all of what i could find to make this... Does it look right?<br /><br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">Famicom to NES Expansion Port Pinout <br />By: Xious Sonenberg<br /><br />FC DA-15            NES 48-Pin DSub EXP<br />1 – Ground         2 - Ground<br />2 - Sound Output         21 – Audio Out<br />3 – IRQ            14 - /IRQ<br />4 - Port #1 &#40;D4&#41; 4017R.4   18 – Joypad #2 &#40;D4&#41;<br />5 - Port #1 &#40;D3&#41; 4017R.3   16 – Joypad #2 &#40;D3&#41;<br />6 - Port #1 &#40;D2&#41; 4017R.2   15 – Joypad #2 &#40;D2&#41;<br />7 - Port #1 &#40;D1&#41; 4017R.1   20 – Joypad #2 &#40;D1&#41;<br />8 - Port #1 &#40;D0&#41; 4017R.0   19 – Joypad #2 &#40;D0&#41;<br />9 - Port #1 CLK 4017R.E   11 – /OE Joypad #2<br />10 - Out2 4016WR.2      45 – Out2<br />11 - Out1 4016WR.1      44 – Out1<br />12 - Out0 4016WR.0      43 – Out0<br />13 - Port #0 &#40;D1&#41; 4016R.1   12 – Joypad #1 D1<br />14 - Port #0 CLK 4016R.E   37 – /OE Joypad #1<br />15 - +5VDC         1 – +5VDC &#40;Out&#41;<br /></div><br />---<br /><br />#2 - FC DA-15 Male port Pin Numbering<br /><br />I also need to verify the port numbering for the male DA-15 EXP connector. Is it:<br /><br />Viewing Male Pins<br />8--7--6--5--4--3--‘2--1<br />15-14-13-12-11-10-9<br /><br />------OR------<br /><br />Viewing Male Pins<br />1--2--3--4--5--6--7--8<br />  10-11-12-13-14-15<br /><br />I can check it myself later, but I figured I'd ask. This should probably be in the Wiki alongside the DA-15 port pinouts.<br />-----<br /><br />#3 - Extra Sound Pins<br /><br />I know that the powerPak rwquires that I bridge, with a 47KΩ resistor, Audio In (EXP Pin 3) to Cart Pin 54 (EXP Pin 9)...<br /><br />I need to know if the 100KΩ resistor + 4.7uF cap mod for 'extra sound' on standard Famicom carts also bridges to the same cart pin (54/EXP#9).<br /><br />Also, is there a tried-and-true method of bridging the pins to perform both mods at once without a toggle switch? If not, what does the powerPak sound like with the 100KΩ resistor and 4.7uF cap, in place of the 47KΩ resistor alone?<br /><br />Is there a happy medium?<br /><br />I'd prefer that the NESpander permits the user to hear the extra sound from both the PowerPak and from FC games such as Akumajou Densetsu without requiring the user to toggle a switch...<br /><br /><strong>EDIT: Looks like the 10K mod goes to EXP pin #40 (cart pin 18), so it's a snap to have both...</strong><br /><br />This is Wiki-worthy too...<br /><br />---<br /><br />I took a bunch of photos of the process of building the latest prototype, and as soon as i wire up the DA-15 port and add the developer sockets, I will create a gallery of them all for you to see.<br /><br />Maybe I can grab a video camera and do a short film that demonstrates the dev board in use... <img src="http://forums.nesdev.com/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /> I guess that depends on whether or not anybody I know has a video camera that i can borrow, as my video equipment is all analogue and I don't want to have to do encoding and editing to get a 3 minute film on-line.<br /><br />Anyhow, this is the info that I need to verify, so that I ensure the correct function of the board with FC expansion devices and audio. Thank you all in advance for any assistance and input!<br /><br />-Xious<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4070">Xious</a> — Sun Aug 15, 2010 4:52 am</p><hr />
